<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16807] DenseVectorField breaks catch-all copyFields</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16807</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently if you setup a copy field with a  * source and a DenseVectorField is present in the schema indexing will fail unless the destination is a DenseVectorField. I think the better behavior is to skip the DenseVectorField during the copy. If we don&apos;t do this the * copyfield is simply broken with a DenseVectorField in the index.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
