                            <comment id="17723917" author="joel.bernstein" created="Thu, 18 May 2023 13:48:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This ticket falls into a broader category called hybrid search where we get vector search to play nicely with lexical search. There are more tickets likely in the hybrid search area coming, &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17723936" author="alessandro.benedetti" created="Thu, 18 May 2023 15:18:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; I think the better behavior is to skip the DenseVectorField during the copy&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What happens right now with point fields for example?&lt;br/&gt;
Anyway, I agree with your proposal and I agree it&apos;s important!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17723941" author="joel.bernstein" created="Thu, 18 May 2023 15:28:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think point fields just get dumped in the catchall field. But it seems like with vectors we really don&apos;t want to do that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17725060" author="joel.bernstein" created="Mon, 22 May 2023 18:08:41 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;The attached PR resolves the issue while preserving the exception in the cases where the copyField source is not *.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A * source copyField was added to the existing test schema which pass. A test proving non * copyField source still throws an exception as it did before. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17725066" author="joel.bernstein" created="Mon, 22 May 2023 18:20:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I plan to merge and backport in a few hours unless there are any objections.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
